# DeutschTest.pro — Cursor Rules

## Project
AI simulator for Goethe-Zertifikat exams (A1, A2, B1).
Stack: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Zustand, Zod, Supabase, Anthropic Claude.

## Security — NEVER violate
- API keys ONLY in .env.local, NEVER in client code
- All Anthropic/ElevenLabs calls — ONLY through /app/api/ server routes
- process.env.SECRET_KEY only in server components and API routes
- Correct answers stored server-side only, NEVER sent to client
- Zod validation on every Claude response
- Never log API keys

## Architecture
- /app — pages and API routes (App Router)
- /components — React components (client-side)
- /lib — server utilities (claude.ts, elevenlabs.ts, supabase.ts)
- /prompts — Claude prompt templates
- /store — Zustand state management
- /types — TypeScript type definitions

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode, no `any`
- Functional components with named exports
- Zustand for client state
- Zod schemas for API validation
- Server components by default, 'use client' only when needed
- Tailwind for styling, no inline styles
- German exam terminology: Lesen, Hören, Schreiben, Sprechen

## Design System
- Light German premium aesthetic (Miele/Braun inspired)
- Background: #FAFAF7, Cards: #F2EFE8, Text: #1A1A1A
- Gold accent (#C8A84B) only on CTAs and icons
- Soft shadows, rounded-lg/xl borders
- Font: Geist Sans

## Exam Rules
- AudioPlayer: play/pause ONLY, no seeking (real exam behavior)
- Timer auto-submits at 0, no going back
- Correct answers never in component props
- Each Hören track plays max 1-2 times as specified
